result.execSummary:
Daniel B Songetay was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Daniel B Songetay was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Daniel B Songetay

records.addlTxt: 01:37 PM Defendant Daniel B Songetay in court, in custody, appearing from Polk County Jail.  Kevin Thomas Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Daniel B Songetay appeared by video means.  Case on for waiver of extradition.  Pine County MN is requesting def's extradition.  Def advised of rights regarding extradition and for an attorney.  Def is sworn in, and affirms his signature on the WOE and affidavit.  Def waives extradition KIV.  Judge signs Waivers, def to be extradited to Pine County MN.  Atty Schmidt makes record/offer in his pending case for OAR 21CT47, def plead as charged, DA to argue for time-served.  Def indicates he wishes to accept that offer.  Court calls case 21CT47.  Case proceeds to Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  Court asks def if they understand the agreement.  Def does.  Court reviews Defs constitutional rights.  Def understands that def is waiving those rights by entering into agreement today.  Court asks Def if they understand Court is not bound by agreement, and could order maximum penalties.  Def understands.  Court asks for plea.  Def enters a plea of Guilty.  Court finds def is making plea knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily.  Court finds a factual basis to accept the plea.  Court finds defendant guilty of Count 1: OAR and orders a JOC.  DA argues for time-served sentence.  Def declines to make astatement to the Court.  Court orders: 30 days jail (time served) $200 (DNA only) court costs.  Def to pay $25/month to begin in April.  Appeal rights provided.  DNA to be provided to the Sheriff before leaving the building.
Unsigned copy of waiver of extradition
